a/20200323/4851910205/suspendida-romeria-rocio-traslado-virgen-almonte-huelva.html|title=Suspendida tambi\u00e9n la romer\u00eda del Roc\u00edo y el traslado de la Virgen|date=2020-03-23|website=La Vanguardia|language=es|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n* [[Spanish Army]] found elderly people abandoned and dead inside retirement homes, according to Defence Minister [[Margarita Robles]]. A criminal investigation was launched.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-52014023|title=Coronavirus: Spanish army finds care home residents 'dead and abandoned|date=23 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020|website=BBC}}</ref>\n* Spain adds 4,000 cases in a single day, reaching 33,000 infected and 2,182 dead.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lasexta.com/noticias/nacional/espana-supera-2000-fallecidos-33000-contagios-coronavirus_202003235e78916695e62a0001b43dda.html|title=Espa\u00f1a supera los 2.000 fallecidos y los 33.000 contagios por coronavirus|date=2020-03-23|website=La Sexta|language=es|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Folgado]], Secretary of State for Budgets and Expenses between 1996 and 2000; for Economy, Energy and SMEs between 2000 and 2002; and for Energy, Industrial Development and SMEs since 2002 until 2004, Deputy of Congress in 2000 and from 2004 to 2008, for the [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]], died aged 75 from COVID-19.\n* [[Alberto Fabra]], former [[President of the Valencian Community]]; [[Juan Cotino]], former president of the [[Corts Valencianes]] and [[Fernando Mart\u00edn \u00c1lvarez]], former president of [[Real Madrid]] were admitted to an [[intensive care unit]] after testing positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/local/valencia/20200323/4859196850/alberto-fabra-empeora-ingresa-en-la-uci-castellon-coronavirus.html|title=Alberto Fabra empeora e ingresa en la UCI por el coronavirus|date=2020-03-23|website=La Vanguardia|language=es|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=